        <?php echo $this->stencil->setHeadline('Common Desktop Environment (CDE)'); ?>
        <p>The <strong>Common Desktop Environment (CDE)</strong> is a desktop environment for <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('Unix', 'OS'); ?> and <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('OpenVMS', 'OS'); ?>, based on the .<?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('Motif widget toolkit', 'IT'); ?> It was part of the UNIX98 Workstation Product Standard, and was long the "classic" <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('Unix', 'OS'); ?> desktop associated with commercial Unix workstations.</p>
        <p>After a long history as proprietary software, CDE was released as free software on 6 August 2012, under the GNU Lesser General Public License, version 2 or later. Since its release as free software, CDE has been ported to <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('Linux', 'OS'); ?> and <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('BSD', 'OS'); ?> derivatives.</p>
